root.HEADER: RADIO X-CEIVER ADMINISTRATION ERROR LOG DATA

AMAP1.name: 1AMAP
AMAP1.b0: Temperature Below Operational Limit. Description: An alarm is raised if the OVCXO temperature falls below the operational temperature. The oscillator frequency depends on temperature. Too low an OVCXO temperature causes timing function disturbances.
AMAP1.b1: Temperature Above Operational Limit. Description: An alarm is raised if the OVCXO temperature rises above the operational temperature. The oscillator frequency depends on temperature. Too high an OVCXO temperature causes timing function disturbances.

BMAP1.name: 1BMAP
BMAP1.b2: GPS Synch Fault. Description: See related fault.

AMAP2.name: 2AMAP
AMAP2.b0: Frame Start Offset Fault. Description: Frame synchronization cannot be maintained for the RBS. If no related faults are present, the frame synchronization will probably recover after a few hours. If this DU is not part of a Synchronized Radio network this fault can be ignored.
